CompatibilityReportCatalog.ReportHeaderText:
General information about using mods: - NEVER (un)subscribe to anything while the game is running! This resets some mods. - Always exit to desktop and restart the game. NEVER exit to main menu! - When playing with mods, save to a new savegame often and make frequent BACKUPS. - Always read the mod description on the Steam Workshop before subscribing. - Abandoned mods can still work fine. They're just unlikely to get updates. - Mod compatible, but not working? Try unsubscribe and resubscribe (while not in game).
Found a mistake? Please fill out this form: https://forms.gle/PvezwfpgS1V1DHqA9

Mod.Name: 81 Tiles (Fixed for 1.2+)
Mod.StabilityNote: To avoid issues at a later stage (including sinking metro stations), always unlock all tiles at the beginning of your game from the mod options, wait a full minute, save, exit to desktop, restart the game and load the save. If a new map doesn't seem to load correctly, unlock all tiles (see above). At map loading, terrain might look distorted for a few seconds. Not everything works outside the 25 tiles area: dams cause tsunamis, disasters and evacuation don't work, pillars changed with No Pillars or Network Skins get reset. Users report a variety of issues, including metro tunnel issues, metro stations sinking with metro lines breaking (see above), and "Out of Range" error messages. Many of these reports lack detailed information and a log file, making it hard to determine if 81 Tiles is indeed the cause of the issue (probably it often isn't).
Mod.Note: When using this mod, it is wise to back up your saves from time to time.
